s well in our world, if we surrender with grace.\n\n- Jennifer\n|\nWhy do I have to do the sewin'? 'Cause I'm a girl? Is that it? It ain't fair, I tell ya!\n\n- Seán Cullen, Hamish X and the Cheese Pirates\n|\nIf you doubt you can accomplish something, then you can't accomplish it. You have to have confidence in your ability, and then be tough enough to follow through.\n\n- Rosalynn\n|\nI'm glad she left me the kids. I'd be lost without them. Lost and bitter. With them here, I'm only bitter.\n\n- Steven Herrick, A Place Like This\n|\nIf you get enough people believing one thing, it's like reality bends itself to allow that to exist.\n\n- Thomm Quackenbush, Artificial Gods\n|\nThe elevator to success is out of order, as you climb; you re-arrange to suit your own call.\n\n- ANIKOR"